  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman comments on Deborah&apos;s name. Chapman criticizes the sermons of a minister named Knapp. She tells of a conversation with Allen Dodge about railroads and abolitionism. She comments on the Bible Convention. She reports on the activities of the Boston Female Anti-Slavery Society, which included sending a copy of their constitution to the members of the Port Plate Society in Haiti. She describes the condition of her husband&apos;s health. Charles L. retold her about his trip to Maine. She mentions Charles T. Torrey. She ends the letter with family news.</subfield>
